programme.title: Ghost Chasers: Exploring the Other Side S2 - "Berengaria Hotel - Cyprus"
programme.desc: Some guests never leave. Does this former luxury hotel located on the island of Cyprus still hosts some of its former guests? Join Josh when he explores the other side.

programme.title: Ghost Chasers: Exploring the Other Side S2 - "Patarei Prison - Estonia"
programme.desc: Josh returns to the Patarei Prison in Estonia, where evil regimes sowed death and destruction, to explore and search for angry spirits and energies from the past.

programme.title: Ghost Chasers: Exploring the Other Side S2 - "Goli Otok Prison Island – Croatia"
programme.desc: Some prisoners are never released. Does Cody find the forever imprisoned on a small island known as the ‘Croatian Alcatraz’?

programme.title: Epic Exploring: Going Local S2 - "Marrakech"
programme.desc: Cody is in Marrakech, Morocco, for a local exploring adventure on BMX-bikes through an old medina, along graffiti walls, night markets and a forbidden hotel.

programme.title: Epic Exploring: Going Local S2 - "Berlin"
programme.desc: Historical Berlin offers Josh two days of adventures and hidden treasures including a former U.S. Spy Station used during the Cold War and an abandoned garage.

programme.title: Epic Exploring: Going Local S2 - "Tbilisi"
programme.desc: Cody discovers the unknown beauty of Tbilisi exploring abandoned Cold War bomb shelters, a derelict weather station and an abandoned cable car station.

programme.title: Epic Exploring: Going Local S2 - "Nantes"
programme.desc: Josh and ultimate traveler Lexie Limitless explore Nantes on a mechanical elephant and inline skates, and discover a deserted mine and a noble house.

programme.title: Garage Dreams S1 - "Psycho"
programme.desc: Greg Maskell's builds are always right on target. Cory and his Dad have worked on this project for years. It may never be ready. A chicken fried real deal from the heart of Dixie. Feels like a journey to the center of the earth for Max and his crew.

programme.title: Garage Dreams S1 - "Back From The Dead"
programme.desc: His car was DOA. So he added some TLC and called it Zombie. The paint brush is still on had in Morris Moman's tool kit. Had one he loved. Now needs 30 more for spare parts. Simply stunning machine restored in all its glory. Annual event in Sin City.

programme.title: Garage Dreams S1 - "Bonneville Community"
programme.desc: The speed records are breaking by the second. From one side of the paddock to the other in record time. Bikes and Japanese influence this café racer world. The best of Series 1 Garage Dreams.

programme.title: Garage Dreams S1 - "Music, Motors and Art"
programme.desc: Michael runs an uber cool build shop with bar and music stage. Craig travelled from Detroit to Melbourne for the love of cars. Murray is obsessed with a bygone era of Nascar.

programme.title: Graveyard Carz S11 - "Amentini, Shaken Not Stirred"
programme.desc: The 1970 Challenger in B7 Blue owned by the Amentinis is finished and ready to be revealed. See every moment of its restoration, from dead to resurrected and detailed to the way it left the factory floor. This is what Graveyard Carz lives for.

programme.title: Graveyard Carz S11 - "Baptism by Fire"
programme.desc: The Pheonix 'Cuda, the car that survived a deadly explosion, is ready for its purification. Its rust and metal are seared away to expose its hidden sins. Thus begins the first stage of its monumental rebirth.

programme.title: Graveyard Carz S11 - "Dougon'it"
programme.desc: Whether it's building an engine, restoring parts, or hiding mannequins, Mark's Cousin Dougie is on it. He's one of the most pivotal Ghouls, working on a vast number of Mopar restoration projects or tasks that are essential to the success of the shop.

programme.title: The Road to Dharma S1 - "Freedom in the Gap at Tungnath"
programme.sub-title: Freedom in the Gap at Tungnath
programme.desc: Emptiness and Power in the Gap. The stunning Tungnath Peak at 13,000 ft, the Feminine Temple above the Masculine. Ken goes from rational doubter to having an experience “beyond understanding” that relates to his deceased sister.

programme.title: The Road to Dharma S1 - "Real Love at Badrinath"
programme.desc: Badrinath – Reverberating with thousands of years of yogic wisdom… But Jeff won’t even wear a helmet. “You try and talk to him, he won’t listen to me,” says Jen. The ebb and flow of relationships and how to sustain them is found here in Badrinath.

programme.title: The Road to Dharma S1 - "True Power in the Hidden Valley of the Flowers"
programme.sub-title: True Power in the Hidden Valley of the Flowers
programme.desc: Before Riding to the Hidden Valley of the Flowers, we get a rare view of the hidden life of the riders in this “real world of yogis” opening scene.

programme.title: Road Trip Masters S1 - "Annapolis, MD"
programme.desc: Brian and Nick are back on the road again and this time rolling into Annapolis, Maryland. Located on the Chesapeake Bay, the boys take in everything that this historic city has to offer.

programme.title: Road Trip Masters S1 - "Newport, RI"
programme.desc: Nick and Brian travel to Newport, RI and experience everything from fresh lobster to the Gilded Age. Then set sail on a classic America's Cup 12 meter yacht.

programme.title: Road Trip Masters S1 - "Cape May, NJ"
programme.desc: Brian and Nick road trip to Cape May, NJ and discover a town that is preserved in the Victorian Era. Join them as they feast on fresh caught seafood, search for diamonds, and blast off on a jet boat!

programme.title: Road Trip Masters S1 - "Gettysburg, PA"
programme.desc: Brian and Nick travel to Gettysburg, PA and experience the battlefield from behind enemy lines. They step back in time and explore the many places that make this town a must stop in Pennsylvania.

programme.title: Road Trip Masters S1 - "Lake Placid. NY"

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.sub-title: Tiki’s Dancing Lesson & Mom and Me
programme.desc: Tiki admires Violet’s dancing. The kids all want Violet to teach them how to dance. Tiki goes to Violet’s home the next day. On his way there his friends tell him dancing is very difficult. He tries to learn some moves from Vick but he feel discouraged. He still continues to learn as Violet keeps encouraging him. But due to his nervousness, he steps on Luna-Loo many times while practicing. Luna-Loo tries to help him relax but none of the method works. Tiki dances in his own way and relaxes. He finally learns how to dance. He realizes he can’t just give up when others say it’s difficult.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.sub-title: The Pink Racket & A Promising Flower
programme.desc: The cubs are playing badminton in the kindergarten. Herbert likes the pink racket. However, he overhears the others say the color pink is only for girls. So he does not dare to take the pink one, even though the one he uses is broken during the match. Then Old Billy joins them. The kids laugh at his floral shirt, but Old Billy doesn’t seem to care. Herbert understands he doesn’t need to pay too much attention to others’ opinions, and decides to use the pink racket.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.desc: The cubs are rehearsing a show. At first, Babu acts well in his role. However, he becomes nervous when Warren and Luna-Loo come to watch the rehearsal. He forgets his lines, and can’t act. Babu thinks he didn’t practice enough but Luna-Loo thinks he has stage fright. He gives his role to Ernie Jo. Then Babu’s dad helps him to overcome his stage fright, and asks him to imagine the audience as fruits. At last, Babu doesn’t feel nervous anymore and acts well in the show.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.sub-title: A Party at Violet’s & Got a Spare?
programme.desc: Violet invites her friends to her home, and has made proper arrangement. She thinks things will go smoothly. However, when her friends come to her house, they don’t want to follow her arrangements. They want to eat cakes and play with the ball. Violet doesn’t know what to do. Her father tells her that she should discuss with her friends about what to do. Violet listens to her friends’ opinions, and they all have fun.

programme.title: Origins Of The Twelve
programme.desc: The two watchmen land on earth and read out the royal edict to the Kitchen God. The Kitchen God takes over the edict with reverence and awe and follows them onto a mass of cloud heading for the Heaven. They look down at the village on the way and find the masses offering sacrifice to the Kitchen God, praying for happiness and good fortune.

programme.title: Origins Of The Twelve
programme.desc: After travelling miles of the sacred Heaven, the Kitchen God comes to the magnificent Hall of Miraculous Mist in the Golden-gated Cloud Palace. He poses a “V” (stands for victory) gesture with Aquila in front of the palace and asks Sonar to draw a portrait of them to mark the occasion. Shortly after, a lowly clerk comes over and brings the Kitchen God into the palace.

programme.title: Origins Of The Twelve
programme.desc: The Jade Emperor orders Aquila and Sonar to come down to earth and assist the Kitchen God with the task. Meanwhile, Rascal the rat finds the royal edict in the Kitchen God’s house and considers it a good opportunity to change the destinies of his family and himself. Rascal hides the edict to keep other animals from seeing it while the Kitchen God sees through his ruse and tries to recapture the edict. They get into an argument and start to scramble for the edict. Just then, Aquila and Sonar break into the house and join the scramble for the royal edict immediately. In the midst of chaos, the royal edict drops into a censer and is burned into ashes.

programme.title: Origins Of The Twelve
programme.desc: The Kitchen God, Rascal, and the two watchmen stand helplessly in front of the censer. Suddenly, a beam of golden light comes from the hearth and the royal edict floats up to the sky. The edict is made public and the news about the upcoming guardian tournament spreads like wildfire. The Kitchen God feels very remorseful for not keeping the secret. However, Aquila says that in that case they don’t need to worry about where to look for the competitors because all the masters will gather at Mount Tai from every corner of the village at that time.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.sub-title: A Whole New World & Bramble the Brave
programme.desc: Little Briar takes Vick’s axe and runs away with little Bramble. Vick follows them to the Pine Tree Kindergarten and meets many little animals there. Ms. Olivia tells him not to be afraid, and soon Vick gets along with the little animals there. Little Briar doesn’t want to join Vick and the other animals, seeming a bit lonely. Ms. Olivia then encourages little Briar to play with the others. At last, the kids at the kindergarten have a good time listening to Vick telling stories of the outside world.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.sub-title: Light Up, Little Guy & Happy Camping
programme.desc: The kids get in a cave of fireflies by chance, where they meet a firefly that can’t glow. They try to help it, but none of the methods work. Coach Mack tells them that a firefly takes in oxygen through air holes on its belly, and the more it takes in, the brighter the light it generates. By utilizing this principle, they encourage the little guy to light up at last.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.sub-title: A Bear’s Gotta Do What A Bear’s Gotta Do & The Watermelon Patch
programme.desc: Young Little Bramble is dependent on his brother doing everything, otherwise he’s gonna cry. Little Briar loves his little brother so he always makes a compromise. He takes him to school, lets him have the bigger apple, and win the game. In math class, Little Bramble is required to answer questions by himself. He fails and bursts into tears. After school, Little Bramble, who’s eager to catch up with Briar, walks home alone and works out math questions all by himself. Now he understands what his brother says, a bear’s gotta do what a bear’s gotta do.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.sub-title: Be Our Guest & Grow Bramble Grow!
programme.desc: Briar and Bramble invite Hoo Hoo to their lair. In order to treat their guest the best they can, they offer Hoo Hoo the best things they have, which turns out to be a great torture to Hoo Hoo instead. Hoo Hoo can’t stand it anymore and even finds herself unable to fly. Luckily, Mama Bear arrives home and saves her. She tells her sons --- Walk in others’ shoes, and then you’ll know what they really want. Then they provide Hoo Hoo with what she really needs, and have a wonderful dinner together.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Coach Mack teaches the kids not to open the door to strangers at class, and the next day, he disguises as a stranger to test the bear brothers. Mama bear cooperates with Coach Mack on the test and leaves home. Coach Mack tries various means to get the bear brothers to open the door, but to no avail. At last, the bear brothers pass the test.

programme.title: Origins Of The Twelve
programme.desc: On the way to Mount Tai, Rascal finds an excuse to run away but Feral Knight gets him back in no time. When they walk up to a dumpling shop, Feral Knight asks Rascal to buy some dumplings without giving him money. Rascal has no choice but to steal a package of dumplings. Just then, the dumpling shop owner finds him and shouts “stop thief”. Feral Knight rushes to the shop owner’s aid and takes the rat together with dumplings away. Feral Knight throws a dumpling to Rascal and eats up the rest of them.

programme.title: Origins Of The Twelve
programme.desc: Fierce the tiger admires the pupils in the Hands of Steel Academy and is simulating the movements in martial arts on the roof. However, he hits himself over the head with a broomstick by mistake and falls down from the rooftop. The master reads him a lecture and tells him to be a good cleaner. Despite the master’s instruction, Fierce never gives up his dream to become a martial artist. He is eager to prove himself a martial artist but is often more of a hindrance than a help.

programme.title: Origins Of The Twelve
programme.desc: Guardian the horse is galloping across the forest to look for the Hands of Steel Academy. He comes to the summit of a mountain and gets lost. Meanwhile, Fierce is having lunch in the forest. Guardian smells a wonderful aroma of steamed buns and walks into the forest to search for them. Suddenly two hedgehogs stand in the way and wants to rob him of some valuables. They run after Guardian at his heels and order him to stop.

programme.title: Origins Of The Twelve
programme.desc: The Kitchen God cannot drive the cloud teleporter and falls into the courtyard of the academy. He gets up and walks into the kitchen to check the hearth. At the same time, Fierce guides Guardian into the west wing room gingerly to show him Mazarine Jar, which however is discovered by the master. They are required to leave the Hands of Steel Academy at once. Guardian begs for the last dinner before leaving and the master agrees reluctantly. Then two animals enter the kitchen and make a fire to cook dinner.

programme.title: Boonie Cubs
programme.desc: The cubs break the trophy they won at the sports meeting. Fear of being criticized by Ms. Oliva, they make up a story that a blue bird attacks Briar and accidentally breaks the trophy. Ms. Olivia sees through their lie and gives them a lesson on honesty. The cubs confess their fault, and fix the trophy together.

programme.title: Boonie Cubs
programme.desc: Bramble decides to keep the caterpillar he finds on his head, and see how it grows up and becomes a butterfly. As time goes by, the caterpillar becomes a pupa, and soon it will turn into a butterfly. But in the process of metamorphosis, Bramble worries that it might get stuck, and tries to help. Ms. Olivia stops him and tells him that it needs to do it itself to get enough strength to fly. Just as they expected, the butterfly finally comes out, dries its wings, and flies.

programme.title: Boonie Cubs
programme.desc: The kids at Pine Tree Kindergarten are discussing what they want to be when they grow up. Vick says he wants to be an inventor and boasts that it’s easy to invent. To prove his point, he wants to invent something to dig holes as well as something for him to fly. However, both inventions meet with failure. Just when he is discouraged, he sees little Briar and Tiki playing paper planes. They are having a little contest. Then Vick gets an idea when he sees Bramble’s balloon. He attaches the balloon to the paper plane, and invents a “balloon plane” which could fly the most distance.

programme.title: Boonie Cubs
programme.desc: The cubs have got a new classmate – Ernie Jo, whose ears look different. A rumor starts that Ernie Jo’s big ears are infectious. Everybody tries to avoid him until Babu touches one of his ear by accident and he’s totally fine. The rumor is cleared and the cubs accept him. They invite Ernie Jo to play hide and seek. With the help of his big ears, Ernie Jo leads the cubs to find Little Vick who has fallen asleep and snores during the game. Now everybody wishes to have big ears like Ernie Jo’s do.

programme.title: Boonie Cubs
programme.sub-title: Rainy Day Fun & The More, The Better?
programme.desc: Violet hates rainy days. She doesn’t get why the others are having fun as usual. She tries to practice her flute, but rain drops cause her flute to get out of tune. Violet gets quite embarrassed and bursts into tears. To comfort her, everybody else gets busy doing funny tricks. Violet stops crying, asks why they enjoy the rain, and finds her own fun on rainy days.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.sub-title: On the Same Page & Field Trip
programme.desc: Briar thinks Bramble is clumsy and can’t seem to cooperate with him well. The bear brothers have a match with Tiki and Babu. Tiki can eat the ice cream brought to him by Babu with his eyes closed, while Briar fails to eat the ice cream in Bramble’s hand. He feels even more frustrated when his face is smeared with ice cream. The cubs play a game after class. Briar still teams up with Bramble to get to the destination. However, Bramble falls behind. Briar chooses the path with apple trees at a junction in consideration of Bramble. When Bramble arrives at the junction, he thinks Briar would choose the bumpy path, and even sprains his ankles on the way. Luckily, Briar shows up just in time. They have a talk and finally understand that they love and know each other very well.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.sub-title: The Hazelnuts & All by My Luna-Loo Lonesome
programme.desc: Tiki, Ernie Jo, and Violet are playing ball in the forest. Tiki happens to find a hazelnut tree when going to pick up the football. He climbs onto the tree to pick the nuts. The trio decide to get these hazelnuts to Violet’s home so her mom can crack them open. Briar and Bramble pass by and help them with the task. When they remove the shells of the hazelnuts, however, the cubs fight to get more of the nuts for themselves. Violet’s mom suggests using the hazelnuts to make a cake, and teaches them to share things with their friends.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.sub-title: Clay Figure & The Toy Car Race
programme.desc: Pine Tree Kindergarten is hosting a handicraft show. Warren and Herbert ask Old Billy to teach them how to make clay figures for the show. Old Billy agrees. Herbert and Warren begin to prepare their clay figures for the show. However, Warren is lazy and skips many steps when making his clay figure. Herbert tells him to follow the steps, but he doesn’t listen. Warren’s figure cracks open during the show. He realizes that he can’t get lazy if he wants to do a good job.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.sub-title: Tiki the Know-it-all & Warren the Chatterbox
programme.desc: The cubs go to harvest some vegetables. Tiki pretends to know everything and tells Babu that loofah is cucumber. Briar points out his mistake. Tiki tries to save face and tells Violet he can fix the dent in her tumbler. Tiki squishes the tumbler and only makes it worse. He sees Violet is really sad and realizes his mistake. Finally he asks Miss Olivia and learns about how to fix the toy.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Joe Croaker picks up a bouncy ball among the grass and takes it home. This small ball bounces around in a way that the frog cannot control. Joe Croaker now is standing on it and the bouncy ball begins to roll down a slope. The frog attempts tries to stop the ball but he simply is not able to mange. It takes the frog some agility and luck to avoid the rocks and tree branches in his way and finally he is stopped by one of McBroom’s dung balls.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Bartle Bee accidentally sets foot in a place studded with numerous full-blown flowers. Overjoyed, he plans to have a good time collecting nectar there. Then there comes a mean bee who tries to beat him up, accusing Bartle of trespassing on his turf. Intimidated, Bartle has to run away from that flourishing land. Flutterby learns of the whole story and decides to help her little buddy punish the bad bee. She paints two horrible huge eyes on the leaves and uses them to scare off the villainous bee. Then Bartle Bee sets up the leaves in the field, but a gust of wind blows them off to the ground, revealing the truth to the vicious bee. In his pursuit of Bartle Bee, the bully bee runs into a big bird which he believes to be a fake one for setting him up. He throws stones at the bird, only to be chased by the furious creature. Just when the bird is about to swallow him, Bartle Bee and Flutterby show up. They distract the bird and save the bee’s life. In the end, the three of them put behind the grudge and become friends.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Joe Croaker comes across a slingshot in the Marsh. He soon realizes that it is a decent swing. The frog then takes a thorough examination of the slingshot. He is convinced that he can shoot some pebbles with this new toy he just found. The pebbles cause damage to the neighboring insects and Joe Croaker could not stop there. He finds a box of pushpins and starts to shoot them.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Cosmo brags about seeing a long train in front of Joe Croaker. The fly can see the world from above in the mid air but Joe Croaker cannot. This upsets the frog. Joe Croaker figures that if he climbs up to the top of the tree, he will be able to get a better view there. But sadly for Joe Croaker, on a long list of the things he can achieve, climbing isn’t one of them. Advised by Cosmo, Joe Croaker makes many failed attempts to climb up the tree. First he tries to do it by sticking the double-sided tape to his limbs, which results in a heavy fall from the tree. Then Cosmo fetches him a rope with a big hook that is intended to be attached to the tree and help Joe up. But it falls and almost has Cosmo crushed. In the end, on Bartle’s suggestion, Cosmo helps Joe Croaker build up a firm ladder which Joe Croaker takes to reach the top of the tree. But when up there, Joe realizes that he is afraid of heights!

programme.title: Boonie Cubs
programme.desc: Briar has a toothache and Vick tells him there are bugs eating his teeth, making him anxious. To get the bugs out, they try many methods, such as gargling water, asking Hoo Hoo to peck the bugs out, and singing to lure the bugs out, all of which are proven to be useless. At last, they go to see Nurse Beakman, then they find out the cause of tooth decay, and learn how to protect their teeth.

programme.title: Boonie Cubs
programme.desc: Violet has a treasure chest, inside which Luna-Loo likes the moon stone the most. That day, Luna-Loo hides the treasure chest somewhere else without Violet’s permission, but what she doesn’t know is that Ms. Lady Jane witnesses the whole thing. The cubs are busy helping Violet look for the chest, while Luna-Loo is invited to Ms. Lady Jane’s office, where she hears Violet’s words about how she cherishes the chest. Luna-Loo realizes what she has done is not right. Ms. Lady Jane comes in. She asks Luna-Loo to return a screwdriver to Vick, and tells her that even though she likes the screwdriver, she can’t keep it because she’s not the owner. Luna-Loo puts the chest back and makes a confession to her friends.

programme.title: Boonie Cubs
programme.sub-title: The Family Visit & You Get What You Put In
programme.desc: Little Briar misbehaves at kindergarten and refuses to apologize to the other kids. Ms. Olivia happens to go to the kids’ home for family visits. Briar is afraid that mom will learn about his behavior at kindergarten, so he tries various means to stop the family visit. Despite of this, Ms. Olivia still meets Briar’s mom. Seeing he could do nothing to stop the family visit, Briar tells the truth. Ms. Olivia tells Briar that he needs to confront his problems, and Briar learns a valuable lesson.

programme.title: Boonie Cubs
programme.sub-title: Tiki the Weatherman & Herby’s Helpful Apples
programme.desc: Old Billy forecasts the weather right, and Tiki asks Old Billy to teach him how to forecast a rainy day. Tiki makes notes and memorizes it. The other kids at Pine Tree Kindergarten plan to have a picnic, and Tiki tells them the weather will be sunny. However, just when the kids are going to have the picnic, it rains. Tiki goes to find Old Billy and asks him what’s wrong with the weather forecast. Old Billy explains that nature changes constantly and that only by studying hard could they make weather forecasts as accurate as possible.

programme.title: Boonie Cubs
programme.sub-title: Kitty the Tiger & The Magic Words
programme.desc: An uninvited guest, Kitty the tiger, sneaks into the drawing class, and shocks the whole class. But later this adorable tiger wins everybody’s heart. They like her, and volunteer to look after her. Kitty makes much trouble. However to make her happy, Prince Tiki lets her have his favorite bag. During naptime, kitty misses her mom so much that she can’t stop crying. Then the kids sing for her to help her sleep. It’s time to say goodbye. Everybody feels sad to part with her. Ms. Olivia promises that Kitty will attend the kindergarten when she grows up, making them happy again.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.sub-title: Herbert on Ice & Warmth in Cold Winter
programme.desc: The forest is covered in snow in winter. Herbert always falls down on the slippery icy road. Vick takes him to learn skating from Coach Mack. However, Herbert is afraid he will fall down and doesn’t want to try. Luna-Loo let him sit on a chair. Herbert thinks it really fun to slide on ice. He tries to learn skating and finds out it’s not as hard as he has imagined. As he skates better and better, he finally understands things are not that difficult once he tries.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.desc: Shadow has an extraordinary taste of tea and who at the same time an excellent brewer. She trains Hoffen to make him acquire the sixth sense. Hoffen spends a lot time watching Shadow brew wine since he finds it’s a little bit beyond him to acquire the subtle sixth sense. The other day Hoffen is lured into the Devoid Bamboo Bush by the two weasels. Star Kid here is completely lost there. He tries every possible direction but still can’t get out of the bush. Hoffen feels desperate when he hears his master’s sound, following which Hoffen finally acquire the sixth sense and walks out the mysterious bush.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.desc: Hoffen and Rascal, under the instruction of Shadow, come all the way to Mount Crouch to locate his last master among the Circle of Twelve, Epsilon the dragon. They are not able to find the spirit of Epsilon rather than his real physical body. The dragon’s spirit is now called Traceless, who challenges Star Child in order to know thoroughly his kung fu skills. Hoffen convinces this mysterious master with a victory. Traceless tells Hoffen that he is trapped by Nian with a lock named Keyless. Hoffen is now determined to smash the lock to free Traceless.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.desc: Hoffen is about to destroy the lock when the Enforcer appears. The crow tries to stop Hoffen but in vain. Hoffen is surprised to see the strange lock Keyless absorb his inner energy each time he hits it. Hoffen calms himself down before he finally finds the weakness of the lock. Star Kid smashes the lock and free Traceless from it. Traceless takes Hoffen to the hideout of Nian, where they can also expect Rascal, who let the weasels lead the way for him.

programme.title: Boonie Cubs
programme.sub-title: A Whole New World & Bramble the Brave
programme.desc: Little Briar takes Vick’s axe and runs away with little Bramble. Vick follows them to the Pine Tree Kindergarten and meets many little animals there. Ms. Olivia tells him not to be afraid, and soon Vick gets along with the little animals there. Little Briar doesn’t want to join Vick and the other animals, seeming a bit lonely. Ms. Olivia then encourages little Briar to play with the others. At last, the kids at the kindergarten have a good time listening to Vick telling stories of the outside world.

programme.title: Boonie Cubs
programme.sub-title: Light Up, Little Guy & Happy Camping
programme.desc: The kids get in a cave of fireflies by chance, where they meet a firefly that can’t glow. They try to help it, but none of the methods work. Coach Mack tells them that a firefly takes in oxygen through air holes on its belly, and the more it takes in, the brighter the light it generates. By utilizing this principle, they encourage the little guy to light up at last.

programme.title: Boonie Cubs
programme.sub-title: A Bear’s Gotta Do What A Bear’s Gotta Do & The Watermelon Patch
programme.desc: Young Little Bramble is dependent on his brother doing everything, otherwise he’s gonna cry. Little Briar loves his little brother so he always makes a compromise. He takes him to school, lets him have the bigger apple, and win the game. In math class, Little Bramble is required to answer questions by himself. He fails and bursts into tears. After school, Little Bramble, who’s eager to catch up with Briar, walks home alone and works out math questions all by himself. Now he understands what his brother says, a bear’s gotta do what a bear’s gotta do.

programme.title: Boonie Cubs
programme.sub-title: Be Our Guest & Grow Bramble Grow!
programme.desc: Briar and Bramble invite Hoo Hoo to their lair. In order to treat their guest the best they can, they offer Hoo Hoo the best things they have, which turns out to be a great torture to Hoo Hoo instead. Hoo Hoo can’t stand it anymore and even finds herself unable to fly. Luckily, Mama Bear arrives home and saves her. She tells her sons --- Walk in others’ shoes, and then you’ll know what they really want. Then they provide Hoo Hoo with what she really needs, and have a wonderful dinner together.

programme.title: Boonie Cubs
programme.desc: Coach Mack teaches the kids not to open the door to strangers at class, and the next day, he disguises as a stranger to test the bear brothers. Mama bear cooperates with Coach Mack on the test and leaves home. Coach Mack tries various means to get the bear brothers to open the door, but to no avail. At last, the bear brothers pass the test.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.sub-title: On the Same Page & Field Trip
programme.desc: Briar thinks Bramble is clumsy and can’t seem to cooperate with him well. The bear brothers have a match with Tiki and Babu. Tiki can eat the ice cream brought to him by Babu with his eyes closed, while Briar fails to eat the ice cream in Bramble’s hand. He feels even more frustrated when his face is smeared with ice cream. The cubs play a game after class. Briar still teams up with Bramble to get to the destination. However, Bramble falls behind. Briar chooses the path with apple trees at a junction in consideration of Bramble. When Bramble arrives at the junction, he thinks Briar would choose the bumpy path, and even sprains his ankles on the way. Luckily, Briar shows up just in time. They have a talk and finally understand that they love and know each other very well.

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.sub-title: Boosting the Ford EcoBoost & Buffing Paint
programme.desc: One of the hottest new rigs on the market is the Ford F150 with the new 6 cylinder eco-boost engine. But is it all it can be? Well, today on GEARZ Stacey takes a new eco-boost powered Ford and shows you some simple upgrades that can boost performance AND fuel economy of this great new engine…..at a price you can afford. Then Stacey rolls in the nastiest, grungiest, barn-find Mustang that you can imagine and shows you the steps and tools required to buff an old nasty paint job back to life. Did we mention that this paint is BLACK!?! All to prove the point that if it can be done with a black car...it can be done with any car…and GEARZ is the show that shows you how to do it!

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: With all the makeovers going on these days, it may surprise you to find that there ARE groups out there that could REALLY use some help. The local volunteer Fire Department is a perfect example of this. Since they are volunteers, nobody gets paid the put their life on the line day in and day out, and the equipment they use is generally hand-me-down stuff from the bigger Fire Departments. Well today on GEARZ, Stacey decides to do something about that by taking a stock Chevy dually pickup, and transform it into a state-of-the-art Brush truck for the local Volunteer Fire Department. The cool thing is, he’s using a lot of aftermarket parts that YOU can use on your project…And if it’s good enough for Firemen that go into harm’s way, you KNOW it is good enough for what you will use it for. So strap in, and let’s go ride a Fire Truck!

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: Station Wagons…Love them or hate them, we all have some stories to tell about them! But most of us have never dreamed that a wagon could be a Hot rod or cool custom…but they can! Today on GEARZ, Stacey shows how much fun a wagon can be when it has an LS engine under the hood, and two four barrel carburetors sitting on it. If you ever wanted to thrash your Dad’s old Wagon, this is the show for you! After that Stacey digs into some of the most asked questions regarding shooting waterborne paint, and finally we take a trip to Texas to see how one body-man created his own business by selling tools, instead of using them. If you are looking for a new career, this could be your answer.

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: When it comes to Cadillac’s, most people immediately think of lowering them down, and cruising with them. However, since the Cadillac Escalade is a great SUV, we thought it would be great to take the Escalade of Country artist Jason Sturgeon, and put a 3 ½” Skyjacker lift on it. Now you have no reason not to go hunting or fishing in style! After that we head to the land of the Predator, and see what it takes to be one of the most successful Monster Trucks of all time with Alan Pezo. Finally, we rub a little of that Monster Truck DNA on SGT. ROCK, as we upgrade the suspension and get it ready to do a little crushing of its own!

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: Everybody knows that you can get almost anything you want on a new car or truck these days. The problem is, if you use your truck for work, “almost” just doesn’t get it. Today on GEARZ, Stacey takes a decked out new truck, and adds some key tools and equipment to make it something that you can literally take to work or play with. After that, we dig into the mysterious world of leather interiors, and show how it is possible for you to buy a top quality leather upholstery kit, and install it yourself. Finally, we roll in the SL-C and show what it takes to put twin turbos on an LS7. It’s gonna be crazy, and it’s only gonna be on GEARZ!

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.sub-title: Project Heavy Metal Suspension & Dax Shepard "Hit and Run" Lincoln Continental
programme.desc: Stacey rolls Heavy Metal back into the shop and begins to lay out some of the incredible modifications that he is going to be doing on this old junk yard ’69 International Cab over truck. A custom four-link air suspension goes on first, and then a slick air brake system to pull this big monster to a stop. A custom exhaust is also laid out, along with numerous other modifications to make this a one of a kind rig. If you have ever wondered if a Cab over could make a cool hot rod, you need to check this out. From there it’s off to the movies as Stacey digs into the impact and influence movie cars have on our lives and culture. To prove that point, He brings in actor Dax Shepard and his cool ’67 Lincoln Continental who are both starring in the new movie “Hit and Run”. So strap in and hold on, ‘cuz we might get airborne on this ride!

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.sub-title: Foxbody Mustang Stick Shift Swap & V8 Interceptor Paint and Body
programme.desc: Everybody knows that 80’s and 90’s cars are hot right now, and one of the most desirable is the Fox bodied Mustang because it’s cheap and offers incredible bang for the buck. Today on GEARZ, Stacey rolls in a 1990 Mustang cop car and shows how easy it is to pull out an automatic tranny, and stuff in a Tremec 6spd so you can shift the gears properly. Then it’s off to the Hot Rod Institute in South Dakota to see the paint and body work that the instructors and students have been doing to the V8 Interceptor. If you thought this ’67 Cougar was wild before, wait ‘til you see this show! Here Kitty,…..Kitty……Kitty….

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: One of the hottest vehicles to hit the gear head world is the Side-by-Side, or Utility Vehicle. Once relegated to just farm or ranch work, the UTV is now something that you will see being used for Hunting, Fishing, Camping, Landscaping….virtually ANY kind of outdoor work or recreation. Of course that means the aftermarket is full of things to make an UTV better. Today on GEARZ, Stacey takes a Polaris Ranger and decks it out with a 3 ½” lift, bigger tires and axles, winches front and rear, and all kinds of other cool things to build an all-terrain vehicle that will really shine on the trail or off. After that he gives you a sneak peek at the new Ironworker that has everybody talking. If you work a lot with metal, you need this machine!

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: What is the most famous car movie of all time? Bullitt?… Vanishing point?... Gone in 60 seconds? Nice guesses, but in terms of influence and sheer popularity, Smokey and the Bandit stands above them all. Stacey takes a look at not only the cultural impact of Smokey and the Bandit, but also it’s most famous character… the black Trans Am. Then, it’s off for a test drive of Year One’s new Burt Reynolds Bandit edition Trans Am to see if it lives up to the true supercar status of the original. Finally, Stacey takes a look and shows you how to use, one of the most mysterious and versatile metal working tools out there… the English Wheel

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: The “Rat Roaster” returns and Stacey finally reveals the kind of power plant that would have made this wild deuce roadster the fastest car in the valley in 1968. And if dual carbs, a blower and about 600 horsepower don’t get you going... maybe the fact that he’s stuffing a 5-speed manual transmission behind it, will! Then, Stacey digs into the Parts Bin to take a look at some of coolest products on the market to help you build your own special ride.

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: Stacey not only brings the “Rat Roaster” ‘32 back in the shop, but he also takes it under the knife as he creates a very unique Dr Jekyll and Mr. Hyde style exhaust system and does some custom modifications to the frame to hide it all from the casual on-looker. If you are interested in taking your project and building it into something truly unique by thinking outside the box… this show will definitely encourage you to do that. Then, Stacey digs into some tips and tricks on how to set your vehicle up for storage for those times when your classic car or hot rod is going to be sitting for awhile unused.

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: In the world of hot rodding, when gear heads gather around and start discussing their projects, invariably the conversation drifts into speculation of what the smallest thing is that you can successfully put a V8 engine in. Stacey pretty much puts an end to that speculation by building a V8 powered Barstool! It’s part go-cart… part garden tractor… part insane... and ALL hot rod, which of course is what Gearz is all about! If you like WILD… then you don’t want to miss this show! Then, Stacey dives into some Muffler Tech to show you what kind of mufflers there are on the market, and give you some tips that might help you make the right decision when the time comes to stick some cool mufflers on your machine.

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: When it comes to classic hot-rod components, nothing gets people going like a multi-carb setup... the Tri-power. Long admired for their stellar performance and macho attitude, the tri-power has become a hard thing to find. So why find one? Why not build your own? Stacey walks you through the process of building your own tri-power out of old derelict parts. After that, he pulls out the big Mopar guns and shows what it takes to put together a six-pack. Then, Stacey gets down and dirty and shows you how to build some simple, ultra strong axle dollies by using some old scrap metal like the kind laying around your garage. Who said gearheads aren’t into recycling?

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: The Banshee is back from paint and we're ready to answer the question… does it still look like a ’95 Miata? Has Stacey shown you how to create a completely different monster? Well, all we can say is the proof is in the paint and you are not going to believe how complete and affordable this transformation really is! Then, Stacey digs into the age-old question: Is it better to restore a car original, or modify it? The answer is up to you as he features a really clean ’68 Plymouth GTX… with some not-so-subtle modifications.

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: Stacey pulls out the tools and starts working metal as he dives into the subject of what to do when your floors are gone… I mean literally gone…nothing there! It’s not as big of a problem as you may think! Stacey rolls in the Rat Roaster and shows you how to create solid metal floors from nothing. This show is loaded with tools and tech that will help you build anything from a small patch panel to a complete floor. While he’s at it, Stacey also covers seat selection and placement so you have a place to plant your seat when you get ready to roll down the street.

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: What do you get when you combine Armor All, Tony Stewart and Stacey David with an iconic vehicle like the Corvette? You get a really cool car called “Ol’ Smoke” and some lucky viewer is going to own it! That’s right, Stacey takes a brand-new ‘Vette' and shows you how to create your own 180+ MPH supercar for a fraction of the cost, using some aftermarket parts. How is that possible?... turbos baby!... and on this show Stacey shows you how to slap a pair of ‘em on the Corvette to run the horsepower numbers to over 600! If you have ever wondered about turbo charging an if it’s right for your vehicle, this is a show you definitely want to see.

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.sub-title: Ol Smoke Corvette Brakes Wheels Tires
programme.desc: Ol’ Smoke is back as Stacey finishes up the transformation of a Brand-new ’08 Corvette, into a full-on super car capable of running with any Ferrari, Porsche, or Lamborghini. It’s a brake upgrade, along with wheels and tires and some custom airbrushing, to not only make the car even more unique, but to also get it ready for it’s new owner to enjoy. Then, Stacey takes Ol’ Smoke out and puts it through the paces showing once again that you can not only have fun building something cool, but also having just as much fun driving it when you are done. No doubt about it, somebody is going to get a special car when Armor All gives Ol’ Smoke away.

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: What is the nastiest project that everyone has to do eventually? That’s right… replacing old, worn out, nasty carpeting. Stacey rolls the Banshee back in the shop and shows you how to bring a very tired interior back to life with some tips and tricks that will help in replacing those old, worn out threads with some new ones. While we are on the subject of interiors, Stacey also digs into one of the best kept secrets in auto restoration… painting a dash and door panels. If you would like to make your dash and door panels look like new again in just a few hours… for very little money… and not have the paint flake off in a few weeks in big chunks, then this is the show you have to see!

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: Stacey takes a look at one of the first aftermarket parts that became available to the public back in the day: the performance air filter… and man does it have an interesting story! From the lowly beginnings of fragile paper elements... to the massive, top secret facilities of industry powers like K&N, the air filter has a heritage that was born and bred on the race track! Then, Stacey digs into one of the neatest tools you’ll ever see and one that every metal worker should own… the Power Hammer. If you are interested in shaping metal and building your own panels, then you need to see this in action.

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: Stacey borrows an ‘07 Jeep JK from a family and jumpstarts their project with the sole purpose of taking it to the next level. However, the real challenge is to build something the whole family will like and still be able to use on the street or off-road. If you’ve ever sat and stared at your project and tried to figure out what the heck to do next or what is the best thing to spend your time and money on… this show is the one to see!

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: Stacey puts the finishing touches on the ’07 Jeep Wrangler with off-road bumpers, body armor, and lights... and builds a very capable off-road rig that is still civil enough to be driven every day. However, just before the Rhea family takes possession of their “new” Jeep, Stacey springs a little surprise on them… He enlists them to help him squeeze a little more performance and gas mileage out of the vehicle, just to prove that anybody can do it! On go the performance air intake, computer upgrades, synthetic oil, and even some slick new seat covers. If you have been reluctant to modify your vehicle because you didn’t think you had the ability…Think again! This show proves that anybody can be a gearhead and make their vehicle better in some way. So now you have no excuse to not be working on something!

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: Stacey takes a well worn, ’73 Chevy pickup that was left for dead in the late 80’s, and starts bringing it back to life by upgrading the suspension and brakes. Not only is this a project that most anybody can do, but it is the start of a three-part series of the major steps that are involved in rebuilding a vehicle. With the way the economy is and the price of new vehicles today, this show demonstrates that there is a better option than buying something new…. bust your own knuckles and build it yourself! Then Stacey sits down with off-road racing legend Ivan Stewart to find out what makes him “the Ironman”.

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: Stacey jumps back into the “KnuckleBuster” project, and deals with an area we can all relate to… a sick engine and transmission. But instead of getting rid of that old worn out vehicle, you can bring it back to life by stuffing in a new engine and transmission; Stacey walks you through the steps to show you just how easy this can be. But, you must be willing to bust your knuckles some and get your hands a little dirty! After that, Stacey puts on the gloves and shows you how to perform a little surgery on a tired rear-end to get the traction that only a locker can supply. Make sure to turn your head and cough!

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: Everybody knows that the area most prone to wear and tear on your vehicle is the interior. Well, that’s OK because today Stacey shows you how to dig into one and bring it back to life without spending a fortune. Whether you just need carpet, door panels, or a complete overhaul, this is something you can do with your own two hands if you are not afraid to get dirty. Then, it’s on to the place you spend most of your time… the seat! As Stacey goes through the steps of reupholstering your old rag-tag seat, you’ll see it can be made as good as new. If you are tired of driving around with an old ratty interior and don’t know what to do, this episode of GEARZ is for you!

programme.title: The Smurfs

programme.desc: In Quarrel Castle, you almost never hear a kind word. Both Selwyn the Warlock and Tallulah, his witch-mate, spend their time quarrelling. Tharp, their pet gargoyle, takes refuge in the Village of Smurfs. But something terrible is going to happen....

programme.title: The Smurfs

programme.desc: Hefty dresses like Smurfette to lure an enamored gnome, Piltkin, away from the Smurf Village. They burrow underground and meet a female gnome who falls in love with Piltkin who then casts Smurfette aside for his new heartthrob.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Once a year, Greedy Smurf makes a special batch of Smurfberry candy. Every Smurf receives a whole year's provision of the smurfiest candy in the whole world. But can a Smurf keep his provision for a whole year? Can the Smurfette?

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Clumsy Smurf's misadventures take him across a river into Pussywillow Hollow. There he meets the Pixies – charming and shapely beings whose enemies, the Wartmongers, will meet the Smurfs in some unforeseen ways.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Grandpa's storytelling has to be heard to be believed. It's not so much that he tells tall tales, as long ones, but this time he gets so carried away that the formula on which he is working boils over... This is bad news. It might mean the destruction of the Village by evil aphids...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: When Smurfette meets this gentle old gypsy woman in the forest and receives a swirling multicoloured dress, she's delighted. How could she know that this woman is really the evil wizard Gargamel in disguise, and that there is a terrible spell on the beautiful dress?

programme.title: Secret Of The Village Well
programme.desc: Why is Clumsy Smurf waiting day and night near the Village well? What is the wish that he wants to be kept secret? How is Gargamel going to be mixed up in this mysterious affair? Is Gargamel going to catch the Smurfs at last?

programme.sub-title: The Smurf Who Could Do No Wrong
programme.desc: Clumsy Smurf, as his name implies, has never been very deft, fleet or graceful. But when Homnibus gives him the Do-No-Wrong Charm, he then becomes the most skilful of the Smurfs. And the others suddenly feel bumbling and slow, which they really resent.

programme.desc: The Smurfs want a poem written for each of them. The pressure overwhelms Poet, so he runs away seeking inspiration. The Wilybeast King captures Poet and forces him to write a poem to cheer up the King's daughter. Poet learns that motivation must come from the heart and cannot be forced.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Oh dear! Sassette has lost a tooth. Papa Smurf explains that if she puts her tooth under her pillow, the Mouse Fairy will bring her a present in the morning. But the next morning there is no present under the pillow. The Mouse Fairy has not been. She has been captured in one of Gargamel’s Smurf traps. And now the evil wizard is concocting a dreadful plan.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: The Smurfs come to the rescue of two children and their grandfather when a mysterious stranger appears and causes their sleigh to crash. Knocking on Gargamel's door for help puts them and the Smurfs in danger...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Smurf Friendship Day is that time in the year when, more than ever, the Smurfs show friendliness to one another. But won't Chlorhydris destroy those good feelings? And how can the Smurfs find a way to exchange Cupid's arrows for something nicer?

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Yes, there can be too much of a good thing. When an accident happens to Papa Smurf's magic formula and he ends up multiplied by two, the Smurfs are elated: two Papa Smurfs can give twice the good counsel and twice the loving that one can. But after a while, things get too complex in the Village. Especially when another accident doubles the number of Gargamels!

programme.title: They'Re Smurfing Our Song
programme.desc: Gargamel casts a spell on Woody's magical pipe to change its music from good to evil. Gargamel captures the Smurfs, but Sassette saves them by telling Gargamel that she loves him. He plays the pipe but the music fades as Gargamel is overcome with feelings of love and releases the Smurfs.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: The Smurfs meet a woodland elf, who teaches them sign language after Gargamel inflicts a no-speaking potion on them.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Smurfette promises Mother Nature that if she creates a blue rose Smurfette will never cut it. But when the white rose becomes blue, Smurfette becomes white. The only way to make Smurfette blue again is for her to cut the rose. She reluctantly cuts the rose, returning nature to normalcy and learning that one cannot always keep a promise.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Due to a wild experiment Clumsy is able to store endless knowledge into his memory. Gargamel captures him, trying to unlock Papa Smurf's invisibility formula, but at the last minute, Clumsy tricks him with the wrong ingredients.

programme.title: Magical Meanie
programme.desc: The Smurfs find a "meanie genie" that refuses to grant them their wishes until they call out the magic word. Unfortunately, Gargamel does some research in his library and finds that "pumpernickel pickles" will send the genie on a magical errand to capture the Smurfs. After Gargamel uses up his three wishes, Papa Smurf sings out the same magic word and the genie has to grant his commands to free the Smurfs, toss Gargamel into the river and bottle himself up forever.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Nobody believes Hefty Smurf when he says that he's seen a huge sea serpent in an old Scottish loch. And later, they don't believe he's seen the evil Gargamel in kilt and tam o' chanter!

programme.desc: Every year, Smurfette snoops around to discover what her birthday presents will be before she receives them. But what this cave also hides is a greedy imp who is not only interested in keeping Smurfette's gifts...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: The village of the Smurfs used to live without a clock. But now suddenly time becomes a precious commodity and Brainy Smurf designs a schedule to take advantage of the new Village clock... Can the Smurfs survive the attacks of time?

programme.sub-title: Marco Smurf And The Pepper Pirates

programme.desc: The Smurfs reach Ancient Spain and gentle Papa Smurf, busy on a crucial experiment, loses his patience. Actually, materially loses it. How it turns out is a surprise for everyone.

programme.desc: Clockwork Smurf is feeling so lonely that, out of compassion, Handy Smurf builds a female companion for him. The trouble is, Clockwork Smurfette does not know she's supposed to have eyes only for her mechanical counterpart, or that she should avoid Gargamel....

programme.desc: The wonderful joy of Christmas for Baby Smurf and everyone else is almost ruined by the evil Chlorhydris who puts a spell on Mr. Nicholas to stop him from spreading holiday cheer. programme.desc: The Smurfs discover a fountain of youth that is guarded by a wicked troll, who steals Papa Smurf's magic book. As the two chase each other all over the countryside, the Smurfs are able to retrieve Papa Smurf's book.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Hogapatra, the hideous, bloated, vulgar Queen of the Nile, cannot get to sleep and this causes huge bags under her eyes. Her beauty recipe requires squeezing sleep from Lazy Smurf...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: How can the Smurfs save this future baby vulture? Right now, it's still in the egg and they must find a way of incubating the bird. And it just happens that the evil wizard Gargamel has found a way of changing himself into a bird to get at the Smurfs...

The genie, called Gourdy, is going to be more of a hindrance than a help in his eagerness to please Farmer Smurf.

programme.desc: It's been a few hundred years since Grandpa Smurf has seen this old toy... It was given to Papa Smurf long, long ago and he does not remember what it does. But Baby Smurf does know that it brings surprises for everyone!

programme.sub-title: A Smurf On The Wild Side, Part I

programme.desc: The Smurflings free the Smurfs from the clutches of Gargamel just in time to get Baby to its first word ceremony. Baby utters the word « Gargamel ». Papa Smurf says that this word indicates that Baby will one day become the Great Chief, as he is aware of the dangers in life.

programme.title: The Smurfs

programme.desc: Harmony Smurf is no longer wanted in the Smurf Choir: his singing is too far off-key. But Papa Smurf gives him an amulet that will make him a vocal virtuoso. Now here comes Hogatha...

programme.desc: Each morning, dew is deposited by water sprites on forest leaves. Wait till you see what happens when Scaredy Smurf gets hold of the dew-making magic wand...

programme.desc: A sinister stranger appears at Gargamel's hovel. He's a bounty hunter. For a price, he always gets what he's looking for... And if Gargamel offers him gold, why, of course he's going to catch the Smurfs!

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: In old China, there is a fortune to be found in Greedy's Smurf cookies and Brainy is the writer. But the opportunity for mischief is too good to miss for Jokey Smurf.

programme.desc: Nasty wizard Gargamel has had enough of the Smurfs' permanent superiority. He decides to destroy their Village once and for all. But the effect is even worse than Gargamel imagined as the Smurfs think that their Village is being torn apart by the antics of the Smurflings.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Smurfs would make delicious meals for the evil wizard Gargamel if it weren't for two things: they're difficult to catch and they're so tiny. Now, suppose there were a formula to change these bite-size snacks into big, juicy square blue meals... Gargamel has an idea...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Clumsy Smurf's misadventures take him across a river into Pussywillow Hollow. There he meets the Pixies – charming and shapely beings whose enemies, the Wartmongers, will meet the Smurfs in some unforeseen ways.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: When the flower fairy Nymph arrives at the Smurf Village, all the Smurfs fall for her charm and wit. And soon they learn that she is to be some sort of Mama Smurf to them...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: In trying to avoid doing his chores, Lazy Smurf finds an old abandoned well with an interesting peculiarity: anything that goes down in the bucket comes back up in its original brand-new condition. But is it good?

programme.desc: In his search for something new, Vanity dons a Gargamel-made magic hat that transforms his face into a mess. Through trickery, Papa Smurf gets the antidote from the wicked wizard and once more, Vanity is beautiful.

programme.desc: When Papa decides to throw a Harvest Moon ball, all the male Smurfs compete in a "Mr Smurf" contest for the honor of escorting Sassette. Gargamel sneaks into the contest after shrinking himself with blue dye, in the hope of capturing all the Smurfs when he returns to normal size. The Smurfs kick him out and Sassette lets Papa escort her.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Gargamel pours a glue-like potion on Clumsy and when anyone touches him, they become stuck to him. The Smurfs become linked to each other until Papa grabs Gargamel's nose. Gargamel, who is annoyed at having all the Smurfs stuck to him, devises a counter-potion and the Smurfs are free once more.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: A swamp monster kidnaps Baby as a gift for a witch. The witch, who thinks no one loves her, is amazed when Baby shows affection. When Papa comes to rescue Baby, he makes the witch understand that the loyal swamp monster has always loved her.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Gargamel and Balthazar command a giant robot to force King Gerard to hand over Clockwork Smurf. When the robot is about to destroy the castle, Clockwork's new, large, and awkward friend Bigmouth defeats the robot. Clockwork is hurt in the battle but Handy fixes him and implants a voice box so he can say "Hi"!

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: The Smurfs' theatrical production of 'Robin Smurf' comes to life as the legendary hero is portrayed by a really good actor...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: The Smurfs take Grandpa Smurf to the King's castle so that he can meet Peewit. But what with one thing and another (especially another), the Smurfs and Peewit are taken aboard a Viking long ship. The Vikings take Peewit to be their mythical Great Warrior, the one who is going to vanquish the Storm King. Can the Smurfs help Peewit out of his quandary?

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: The Smurfs don't want to be pirates stealing gold from passing galleons. But they fall under the spell of the magic Clamulet and become the crew of Bluebeak the Parrot.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: The Smurflings accompany Woolly on his mission to shear wool for winter clothes. They must overcome obstacles such as Gargamel, a wolf and finally a shepherd boy who will not accept smurfberries as payment for the wool. The Smurflings and Woolly develop respect for one another through their travels.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Smurfs would make delicious meals for the evil wizard Gargamel if it weren't for two things: they're difficult to catch and they're so tiny. Now, suppose there were a formula to change these bite-size snacks into big, juicy square blue meals... Gargamel has an idea...

programme.desc: Whatever Brainy Smurf says, the Clockwork Smurf devised by Handy has feelings just like any normal blue Smurf. When the evil wizard Gargamel and his apprentice Scruple find the tiny contraption and fit it with a heart of stone, the Smurfs are in for a bad time...

programme.title: The A-Maze-Ing Smurfs
programme.desc: Jokey Smurf is dying to meet Melchior the Magnificent, creator of the famous Vanishing Box trick. Can Gargamel catch the Smurfs in Melchior's Amazing Maze?

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Simon is lost in the forest and in search of his parents. Simon is the son of a couple of giants. The Smurfs try to bring him home, but then Gargamel interrupts the party.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: In another Smurf theatrical super-production based – very loosely – on Alexandre Dumas' characters, a masterpiece of the stage is created, with a few lines from Romeo and Juliet thrown in.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: When Brainy loses his glasses, he drops things, runs into objects, and becomes just as helpless as Clumsy, who now has to read to Brainy and help him get around. This experience makes Brainy feel guilty for the way he always made fun of Clumsy. He treats him with more respect once he receives a new pair of glasses.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Oh, sure, kickball (or smurfball, as they call it) is all right for a while. But it gets sort of boring after a few centuries. Now there's this new game that has been invented by a nondescript Smurf, a game where you hit a ball with a stick and send it into a gopher hole...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: This is the dramatic, moving story of the friendship between Smurfette and her pet mouse. A sad event reduces Smurfette to tears... Can the Smurfs comfort the despairing Smurfette?

programme.title: Heavenly Smurfs
programme.desc: Once again, Gargamel's infallible plan to catch the Smurfs has been foiled. But the Smurfs play a trick on him: disguised as tiny blue angels, they will teach him to mend his ways...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Thinking Baby Smurf is a leprechaun, two poachers kidnap him and try to get the small one to tell them where his pot of gold is hidden. Papa Smurf organizes everyone to attack the villains with Smurfberry pies so Baby can escape.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Papa Smurf's worries make him break into a rash of worrywarts. The only way to relieve him of his bout of indecision-inducing disease is to have him rub the horn of a Wartmonger, a sloppy, slimy, stupid and brutal enemy of the Pussywillow Pixies...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Accidents do happen. This time it is Jokey Smurf's mistake that ends up with his shadow coming to independent life! And the shadow loves to play practical jokes on the whole population of the Village of the Smurfs...

programme.title: The Horn Of Plenty
programme.desc: Mother Nature always does her best, but this time she's gone wrong. Her wand gets the wrong results and she accidentally damages the Autumn harvest. Now the Smurfs and all the forest animals face a lean and hungry winter. The only place where the Smurfs could get food would be the Land of Plenty. But Gargamel steals the famed Horn of Plenty to lure the Smurfs.

programme.title: The Magic Earrings
